Joh 13:21 When Jesus had said this, He became troubled in spirit, and testified and said, &ldquo;Truly, truly, I say to you, that one of you will betray Me.&rdquo;
Joh 13:22 The disciples began looking at one another, at a loss to know of which one He was speaking.
Joh 13:23 There was reclining on Jesus&rsquo; bosom one of His disciples, whom Jesus loved.
Joh 13:24 So Simon Peter *gestured to him, and *said to him, &ldquo;Tell us who it is of whom He is speaking.&rdquo;
Joh 13:25 He, leaning back thus on Jesus&rsquo; bosom, *said to Him, &ldquo;Lord, who is it?&rdquo;
Joh 13:26 Jesus then *answered, &ldquo;That is the one for whom I shall dip the morsel and give it to him.&rdquo; So when He had dipped the morsel, He *took and *gave it to Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot.
Joh 13:27 After the morsel, Satan then entered into him. Therefore Jesus *said to him, &ldquo;What you do, do quickly.&rdquo;
Joh 13:28 Now no one of those reclining at the table knew for what purpose He had said this to him.
Joh 13:29 For some were supposing, because Judas had the money box, that Jesus was saying to him, &ldquo;Buy the things we have need of for the feast&rdquo;; or else, that he should give something to the poor.
Joh 13:30 So after receiving the morsel he went out immediately; and it was night.
A New Commandment# Joh 13:31 Therefore when he had gone out, Jesus *said, &ldquo;Now is the Son of Man glorified, and God is glorified in Him;
Joh 13:32 if God is glorified in Him, God will also glorify Him in Himself, and will glorify Him immediately.
Joh 13:33 &ldquo;Little children, I am with you a little while longer. You will seek Me; and as I said to the Jews, now I also say to you, &lsquo;Where I am going, you cannot come.&rsquo;
Joh 13:34 &ldquo;A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another, even as I have loved you, that you also love one another.
Joh 13:35 &ldquo;By this all men will know that you are My disciples, if you have love for one another.&rdquo;
Jesus Foretells Peter&rsquo;s Denial# Joh 13:36 Simon Peter *said to Him, &ldquo;Lord, where are You going?&rdquo; Jesus answered, &ldquo;Where I go, you cannot follow Me now; but you will follow later.&rdquo;
Joh 13:37 Peter *said to Him, &ldquo;Lord, why can I not follow You right now? I will lay down my life for You.&rdquo;
Joh 13:38 Jesus *answered, &ldquo;Will you lay down your life for Me? Truly, truly, I say to you, a rooster will not crow until you deny Me three times.
====
