Joh 8:31 So Jesus was saying to those Jews who had believed Him, &ldquo;If you continue in My word, then you are truly disciples of Mine;
Joh 8:32 and you will know the truth, and the truth will make you free.&rdquo;
Joh 8:33 They answered Him, &ldquo;We are Abraham&rsquo;s descendants and have never yet been enslaved to anyone; how is it that You say, &lsquo;You will become free&rsquo;?&rdquo;
Joh 8:34 Jesus answered them, &ldquo;Truly, truly, I say to you, everyone who commits sin is the slave of sin.
Joh 8:35 &ldquo;The slave does not remain in the house forever; the son does remain forever.
Joh 8:36 &ldquo;So if the Son makes you free, you will be free indeed.
Joh 8:37 &ldquo;I know that you are Abraham&rsquo;s descendants; yet you seek to kill Me, because My word has no place in you.
Joh 8:38 &ldquo;I speak the things which I have seen with My Father; therefore you also do the things which you heard from your father.&rdquo;
You Are of Your Father the Devil# Joh 8:39 They answered and said to Him, &ldquo;Abraham is our father.&rdquo; Jesus *said to them, &ldquo;If you are Abraham&rsquo;s children, do the deeds of Abraham.
Joh 8:40 &ldquo;But as it is, you are seeking to kill Me, a man who has told you the truth, which I heard from God; this Abraham did not do.
Joh 8:41 &ldquo;You are doing the deeds of your father.&rdquo; They said to Him, &ldquo;We were not born of fornication; we have one Father: God.&rdquo;
Joh 8:42 Jesus said to them, &ldquo;If God were your Father, you would love Me, for I proceeded forth and have come from God, for I have not even come on My own initiative, but He sent Me.
Joh 8:43 &ldquo;Why do you not understand what I am saying? It is because you cannot hear My word.
Joh 8:44 &ldquo;You are of your father the devil, and you want to do the desires of your father. He was a murderer from the beginning, and does not stand in the truth because there is no truth in him. Whenever he speaks a lie, he speaks from his own nature, for he is a liar and the father of lies.
