Zechariah# possible title: Israel&rsquo;s Messiah to the Nations# (Phrased + Indented)# • Why study the book of Zechariah? • It reveals behind the scenes Spiritual warfare • It reveals Israel&rsquo;s future kingdom and the nations under it. • Because God remembers his promises (Meaning of Zechariah). • IT is because of the prophecy of this book and teh book of Haggai that the temple was rebuilt. Ezra 4:5 After 70 years God raised up a man named Cyrus to open the door to Juda&rsquo;s return to the land. This return happened in three waves. The first wave was led by a man named Zerubabel. This first return is the time at which the prophecy of Zechariah is given. Upon Juda&rsquo;s return to Jerusalem they first rebuilt the altar of the Lord and reestablished sacrifices. Also, the Temple was to be rebuilt with donations of material and money (Ezra 3:1–7) but up to the point where Zechariah&rsquo;s prophecy begins, only the foundation has been laid. Opposition from the Samaritans has delayed the work about 18 years.
