Four Chariots# Now I lifted up my eyes again and looked, and behold, four chariots were coming forth from between the two mountains; and the mountains were bronze mountains. With the first chariot were red horses, with the second chariot black horses, with the third chariot white horses, and with the fourth chariot strong dappled horses. Then I spoke and said to the angel who was speaking with me, &ldquo;What are these, my lord?&rdquo; The angel replied to me, &ldquo;These are the four spirits of heaven, going forth after standing before the Lord of all the earth, with one of which the black horses are going forth to the north country; and the white ones go forth after them, while the dappled ones go forth to the south country. &ldquo;When the strong ones went out, they were eager to go to patrol the earth.&rdquo; And He said, &ldquo;Go, patrol the earth.&rdquo; So they patrolled the earth. Then He cried out to me and spoke to me saying, &ldquo;See, those who are going to the land of the north have appeased My wrath in the land of the north.&rdquo; The word of the LORD also came to me, saying, &ldquo;Take an offering from the exiles, from Heldai, Tobijah and Jedaiah; and you go the same day and enter the house of Josiah the son of Zephaniah, where they have arrived from Babylon. &ldquo;Take silver and gold, make an ornate crown and set iton the head of Joshua the son of Jehozadak, the high priest. &ldquo;Then say to him, &lsquo;Thus says the LORD of hosts, &ldquo;Behold, a man whose name is Branch, for He will branch out from where He is; and He will build the temple of the LORD. &ldquo;Yes, it is He who will build the temple of the LORD, and He who will bear the honor and sit and rule on His throne. Thus, He will be a priest on His throne, and the counsel of peace will be between the two offices.&rdquo;&rsquo; &ldquo;Now the crown will become a reminder in the temple of the LORD to Helem, Tobijah, Jedaiah and Hen the son of Zephaniah. &ldquo;Those who are far off will come and build the temple of the LORD.&rdquo; Then you will know that the LORD of hosts has sent me to you. And it will take place if you completely obey the LORD your God.
Message #3 -# In the fourth year of King Darius, the word of the LORD came to Zechariah on the fourth day of the ninth month, which is Chislev. Now the town of Bethel had sent Sharezer and Regemmelech and their men to seek the favor of the LORD, speaking to the priests who belong to the house of the LORD of hosts, and to the prophets, saying, &ldquo;Shall I weep in the fifth month and abstain, as I have done these many years?&rdquo; Then the word of the LORD of hosts came to me, saying, &ldquo;Say to all the people of the land and to the priests, &lsquo;When you fasted and mourned in the fifth and seventh months these seventy years, was it actually for Me that you fasted? &lsquo;When you eat and drink, do you not eat for yourselves and do you not drink for yourselves? &lsquo;Are not these the words which the LORD proclaimed by the former prophets, when Jerusalem was inhabited and prosperous along with its cities around it, and the Negev and the foothills were inhabited?&rsquo;&rdquo;
Then the word of the LORD came to Zechariah saying,
&ldquo;Thus has the LORD of hosts said, &lsquo;Dispense true justice and practice kindness and compassion each to his brother; and do not oppress the widow or the orphan, the stranger or the poor; and do not devise evil in your hearts against one another.&rsquo; &ldquo;But they refused to pay attention and turned a stubborn shoulder and stopped their ears from hearing. &ldquo;They made their hearts like flint so that they could not hear the law and the words which the LORD of hosts had sent by His Spirit through the former prophets; therefore great wrath came from the LORD of hosts. &ldquo;And just as He called and they would not listen, so they called and I would not listen,&rdquo; says the LORD of hosts; &ldquo;but I scattered them with a storm wind among all the nations whom they have not known. Thus the land is desolated behind them so that no one went back and forth, for they made the pleasant land desolate.&rdquo;
Then the word of the LORD of hosts came, saying, &ldquo;Thus says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;I am exceedingly jealous for Zion, yes, with great wrath I am jealous for her.&rsquo; &ldquo;Thus says the LORD, &lsquo;I will return to Zion and will dwell in the midst of Jerusalem. Then Jerusalem will be called the City of Truth, and the mountain of the LORD of hosts *will be called *the Holy Mountain.&rsquo; &ldquo;Thus says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;Old men and old women will again sit in the streets of Jerusalem, each man with his staff in his hand because of age.
&lsquo;And the streets of the city will be filled with boys and girls playing in its streets.&rsquo; &ldquo;Thus says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;If it is too difficult in the sight of the remnant of this people in those days, will it also be too difficult in My sight?&rsquo; declares the LORD of hosts. &ldquo;Thus says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;Behold, I am going to save My people from the land of the east and from the land of the west; and I will bring them back and they will live in the midst of Jerusalem; and they shall be My people, and I will be their God in truth and righteousness.&rsquo; &ldquo;Thus says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;Let your hands be strong, you who are listening in these days to these words from the mouth of the prophets, those who spoke in the day that the foundation of the house of the LORD of hosts was laid, to the end that the temple might be built. &lsquo;For before those days there was no wage for man or any wage for animal; and for him who went out or came in there was no peace because of his enemies, and I set all men one against another. &lsquo;But now I will not treat the remnant of this people as in the former days, &rsquo; declares the LORD of hosts. &lsquo;For there will be peace for the seed: the vine will yield its fruit, the land will yield its produce and the heavens will give their dew; and I will cause the remnant of this people to inherit all these things. &lsquo;It will come about that just as you were a curse among the nations, O house of Judah and house of Israel, so I will save you that you may become a blessing. Do not fear; let your hands be strong.&rsquo; &ldquo;For thus says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;Just as I purposed to do harm to you when your fathers provoked Me to wrath,&rsquo; says the LORD of hosts, &lsquo;and I have not relented, so I have again purposed in these days to do good to Jerusalem and to the house of Judah. Do not fear! &lsquo;These are the things which you should do: speak the truth to one another;